      "message": "I felt that regex is too heavy for this simple check, and that was probably the reason why [config/project_name.go] was implemented in the same way.\n\n```\n# with ^[a-z](?:[a-z0-9\\-]){4,28}(?:[a-z0-9])$\nBenchmarkFOO-16           421909              2798 ns/op\nBenchmarkFOO-16           417398              2797 ns/op\nBenchmarkFOO-16           418382              2828 ns/op\n\n# w/o regex\nBenchmarkFOO-16          1871151               640 ns/op\nBenchmarkFOO-16          1880722               635 ns/op\n```\n\nHaving said, I don\u0027t think we need this micro(?) optimization until we need it, and regex is easier to maintain? WDYT?\n\n[config/project_name.go]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/config/project_name.go",
